<h1>About Little Boracay Calatagan, Batangas</h1>

<p>
Little Boracay is one of the most recognized sandbar destinations in 
<strong>Calatagan, Batangas</strong>. Known for its clear shallow waters, 
wide white sand areas, and the iconic floating bamboo cottages anchored 
offshore, the destination has become a popular coastal escape for travelers 
throughout the Philippines.
</p>

<p>
Situated along the western coastline of Batangas facing the South China Sea, 
Little Boracay offers a unique tidal sandbar environment where shallow waters 
and open sea views create a relaxing beach experience. Visitors frequently 
travel to the area for swimming, floating cottage gatherings, and scenic 
coastal photography.
</p>

